---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Mari Lescaille" description="Staff software engineer working on consumer identity at Netflix, writing poems and stories in her free time. Havana → San Francisco, with receipts.">
<style>
  h1{font-size:clamp(28px,5.4vw,40px);font-weight:500;line-height:1.15;letter-spacing:-.01em;padding:44px 0 0}
  .intro{padding:20px 0 0;font-size:19px}
  .intro p+p{margin-top:18px}
  .intro .tech{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.86em;background:var(--purple-soft);border-radius:4px;padding:1px 6px}
  .intro .es{font-style:italic}
  section{padding:56px 0 0}
  .timeline{margin:24px 0 0 4px;border-left:2px solid var(--line);padding-left:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:26px}
  .stop{position:relative}
  .stop::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:-31px;top:7px;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--purple-strong);border:2px solid var(--paper)}
  .stop .years{font-family:var(--mono);font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--pink)}
  .stop h3{font-size:18.5px;font-weight:600;margin:2px 0 4px}
  .stop p{color:var(--muted);font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.55;max-width:60ch}
  .coda{margin-top:36px;font-style:italic;font-size:19px;color:var(--purple)}
</style>
<h1>About</h1>
<div class="intro">
  <p>I'm Mari. I'm a staff software engineer at Netflix, where I work on consumer identity — the systems that know which device is yours, which session to end, which of two hundred million accounts just signed in. I've been writing software for fifteen years and poems for longer, in two languages <span class="es">(a veces en las dos a la vez)</span>.</p>
  <p><span class="es">Cuba → Uruguay → United States.</span> I'm a software engineer by trade, an entrepreneur by life school, (grand)daughter, friend. In my free time I write poems and short stories. I tend to write short essays and like conciseness.</p>
  <p>I learn by building, so most of what lives here is something you can read, run, or play with: essays on <span class="tech">debugging</span> and <span class="tech">distributed&nbsp;systems</span>, explorable simulations, poems, stories, talks.</p>
  <p>For more technical writing, find me at <a href="https://mlescaille.medium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mlescaille on Medium<span class="external-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>.</p>
</div>

<section aria-labelledby="trajectory-label">
  <div class="sec-label" id="trajectory-label"><span class="es">trayectoria</span> a trajectory</div>
  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2013–2016</div>
      <h3>Origins — Havana</h3>
      <p>Founded VenusIT / DevGirls at the Universidad de las Ciencias Informáticas to make women in computing visible, co-organized the first Grace Hopper Celebration held in Cuba, and ran a small consulting firm with two friends at a time when private firms were illegal. This site's colors come from those VenusIT posters.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2017</div>
      <h3>The leap</h3>
      <p>Havana → San Francisco through the Silicon Valley Internship Programme. Taught a real monolith-to-microservices migration on stage at Latinity — in Spanish — and joined Survata as a backend engineer.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2018–2019</div>
      <h3>The voice wave</h3>
      <p>Founded VoiceFirst Weekly: 132 daily briefings on voice technology, shipped on Alexa, Google Assistant, Spotify, and Samsung Bixby — as one of Bixby's early developer partners.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2019–2020</div>
      <h3>The systems years</h3>
      <p>Production MySQL 5.7 → 8 migration, an API documentation initiative adopted company-wide, shared AWS libraries — then a deliberately engineered move to Netflix.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2020 →</div>
      <h3>Netflix + the craft</h3>
      <p>Senior, then staff, engineer on consumer identity. Nights and weekends: atomic essays, algorithmic and visual poetry, small bets — the engineering and the poetry from the same hands.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stop">
      <div class="years">2026 →</div>
      <h3>The AI reboot</h3>
      <p>Same playbook as 2018 — adopt the frontier early, hands on the tooling — new wave. This site is part of it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="coda">Think, feel.</p>
</section>
</Base>
